    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cheney for Vice President? Some Early Reviews</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Shaun Breidbart letter questions Dick Cheney's change of voter registration in order to avoid constitutional problem as Gov George Bush's vice presidential running mate (July 25 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report that a few days before being chosen by George W. Bush to be his running mate, Dick Cheney flew to Wyoming to change his voter registration to avoid a constitutional problem (news article, July 25). The Constitution, you note, prohibits Electoral College members from selecting ''inhabitants'' of their state as both president and vice president.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report that a few days before being chosen by George W. Bush to be his running mate, Dick Cheney flew to Wyoming to change his voter registration to avoid a constitutional problem (news article, July 25). The Constitution, you note, prohibits Electoral College members from selecting ''inhabitants'' of their state as both president and vice president.</p>
        <p>Regardless of his voter-registration change, Mr. Cheney has most recently lived in Texas, effectively making him from Texas despite his owning property in Wyoming and filling out a form there. Do we want someone as vice president who would act in this way for political gain?</p>
        <p>SHAUN BREIDBART  Pelham, N.Y., July 25, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
